description:
There are big reasons why this place has been so popular for years.  I am talking years, as in since 1991.  That means I had a fat perm and wore leggings when Fringale debuted.  And I am wearing leggings again now.  

So Saturday night's birthday dinner was everything this restaurant has lived up to be--- the most perfect bistro flair.  The big reasons are as follows:

1. Although only 4 seats at the bar, it is well equipped with all you lushes' favorites and a friendly bartender;
2. Cute French waiters;
3. Sweetbreads were the best I've ever had;
4. Duck Confit was excellent;
5. Loved the lentil du puy, even though generally not a lentil fan at all;
6. They managed to place a candle on the creme brulee...

Great food, great service, great restaurant.
